\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying constructor accessibility**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the implicit default constructor is public if the class is public and has no declared constructors. The answer is yes! However, there's a potential issue to consider: when localMBean = createMBean(null, ...) returns a DynamicMBean object, it might actually instantiate a new BaseModelMBeanTest. I'm noting that this could be an important detail to keep in mind when working with MBeans. It’s all about ensuring I understand these subtle nuances!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Connector setup**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the Connector HTTP port maybe causing some flaking with timeouts. It seems like it already exists. However, adding a set after starting it shouldn't be an issue. According to the instructions, we may not need to run tests ourselves, so I guess we won’t. I might take a look at the git diff to better understand what’s been changed. It seems like there’s a lot to consider here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JwICdQYscy5bVmFYi2i4wzXi|fc_0006c15b3f7cd7d4016a3972da64848196b110c0c20c201259", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/src/test/java/tomcat/BaseModelMBeanTest.java tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/src/test/java/tomcat/ConnectorProtocolIntrospectionTest.java", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 570, "output": 1172, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40142, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782149832007, "responseId": "resp_0006c15b3f7cd7d4016a3972c8a0f4819688025675351320e0"}}
